21/01/2011
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A military court in Bucharest convicted 11 military officers Thursday (January 20th) of stealing weapons from an arms depot near the capital in 2009. The defendants got punishments ranging from six months suspended sentence to 15 years in prison. They were accused of stealing more than 50 weapons. Several high-ranking officers, including the head of the air force, were fired after the incident. (Agerpres, Realitatea - 20/01/11)
